snippet: Miami-Dade County officials are expected to abolish the city of Islandia, a desolate chain of 33 islands that mid-century land developers had hoped to turn into a rollicking resort town.
abstract: Miami-Dade County officials are expected to abolish the tiny city of Islandia, a desolate chain of 33 islands that mid-century land developers had hoped to turn into a resort town; most of Islandia, which has only five residents, sits on land of Biscayne National Park.
lead_paragraph: Miami-Dade County officials are expected to abolish the city of Islandia, a desolate chain of 33 islands that mid-century land developers had hoped to turn into a rollicking resort town.

headline.seo: Islandia, a Florida City That Never Was
headline.main: A Florida City That Never Was
